verse_part: from those to whom it is due
and she will watch over you
is the one who goes in
And those who diligently seek me
But he who sins against me
for yourself, And if you scoff
one who pretends to be rich
of the one who has understanding
He who provokes him to anger
Or like one who lies down
those who are being taken away
Yes, the honey from the comb
those who are given to change
Than for you to be placed lower
And the evil report about you
he will become weary of you
But he who is a companion
and he will give you comfort
and you will be proved a liar
and you will be found guilty
